case_vignette: A 62-year-old man presents to the emergency department with skin lesions. The patient states that he has felt itchy recently, then noticed skin lesions that broke out this morning prompting him to come to the emergency department. The patient states that he recently went camping and hiking in the woods. The patient drinks 1-2 beers per day and smokes 1 pack of cigarettes per day.
